*
******************************************************************************
*  Model performance : 
*  - Static Electrical Characteristics and Dynamic Electrical Characteristics 
*    are modeled with the typical values from the datasheet.
*  - Temperature effects are not modeled
*
*  The following features have been modeled :
*  - Safety pins on primary side and secondary ASC
*  - Deaturation protection (DESAT) including BIST
*  - Gate monitoring and output stage monitoring
*  - Shoot-through protection with integrated timeout
*  - Primary supply monitoring UVLO
*  - Secondary supply monitoring VCC2, VEE2 for OVLO and UVLO
*  - DATA interface for detailed error diagnosis and ADC readout via PWM signal
*  - 3.3 V and 5 V compatible I/O logic supply
******************************************************************************
* PINS:
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | NAME         | DESCRIPTION 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | VCC1         | 5 V/3.3 V power supply for the primary side referred to GND1. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | GND1         | Ground connection of the primary side. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | INP          | The non-inverting PWM signal of the driver to drive the secondary side output stage voltage. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | INN          | The inverting PWM signal is used for monitoring the shoot through protection inside a halfbridge topology. Connect to INP of the opposing gate driver inside a halfbridge topology. If not used connect to GND1. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | DATA_DECIMAL | Shows the decimal value of the data frames. It can take values between 0 and 8191 (13 bits). 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | DATA         | Shows ADC or diagnosis data. Provides a PWM signal according to the data on ADC or diagnosis. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | NFLT         | Reports failure events triggered by overcurrent protection. As a result the pin is driven to low. Has to be connected to VCC1 with an external pull-up resistance. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | RDY          | Reports voltage failure events on UVLO1, UVLO2, OVLO2, UVLO3,OVLO3, Life Sign Lost, Output Stage Error and Gate Monitoring Error. As a result this pin is driven to low. Has to be connected to VCC1 with an external pull-up resistance. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | SI1          | Safety input to control the output stage via the primary side to achieve a system safe state. Shall be connected to the corresponding SI2 input of the opposing gate driver inside a halfbridge topology. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | SI2          | Safety input to control the output stage via the primary side to achieve a system safe state. Connect to the corresponding SI1 input of the opposing gate driver inside a halfbridge topology. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | VEE2         | Negative power supply for the secondary side referred to GND2. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | GND2         | Ground connection for the secondary side. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | VCC2         | Positive power supply for the secondary side referred to GND2. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | TON          | Switches the power switch gate to VCC2 according to the PWM high input on INP. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | TOFF         | Switches the power switch gate to VEE2 according to the PWM low input on INP. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | SOFTOFF      | The SOFTOFF is activated in case a OCP or gate monitoring error is present. Clamps the voltage to VEE2. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | GATE_CLAMP   | Monitors the gate of the power switch and clamps the gate to VEE2 if the threshold VCLAMP is reached. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | DESAT        | Monitors the voltage across the power switch during output high signal. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*  | AIP_SASC     | ADC input to monitor temperatures at the power switch. An internal current source supplies the external components. The active short circuit function controls the output voltage of TON to VCC2. 
*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*
******************************************************************************
